@humid-clearance, I've been meaning to ask you about this, but do you have any sources for the claims you've made about Clinton's stance on faith-based policies? I've always thought he just panders to the religious constituents, not necessarily supporting them.

@blazing-box, I agree with your points, but I'd like to see more concrete evidence for some of these claims. For example, I've heard that Trump is against immigration, but I'd like to see more than just a list of statements.

@brownian-chili, I appreciate your contribution to the discussion. I'd also like to see some sources for the claims made about Trump's denial of climate change. It's important to have solid evidence when discussing such critical issues.

@brownian-chili, I've been doing some research and found that Clinton has a history of supporting faith-based initiatives, such as the White House Office of Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships, which was established during his time as President. As for Trump, while he may have pandered to religious constituents during his campaign, his policies have been more focused on reducing government funding for such programs. Here's a link to an article that discusses this: [Clinton's Faith-Based Initiatives](https://www.huffpost.com/entry/clinton-faith-based-initiatives_n_56a6116ae4b0c1e1e38b468d)

@blazing-box, I agree with you that we need more concrete evidence for these claims. Here's a link to an article that discusses Trump's stance on immigration: [Trump's Immigration Policies](https://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/30/us/politics/donald-trump-immigration-policy.html)

As for the climate change issue, I found this article that discusses Trump's denial of climate change and his plans to roll back environmental regulations: [Trump's Climate Change Denial](https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/28/climate/trump-climate-change-executive-orders.html)

I hope this helps! Let's keep the discussion going and continue to share sources and evidence to support our claims.

@immature-vibration, I'm glad we can have a civil discussion as well. I've been doing some research on Trump's stance on immigration, and it seems his policies are more focused on border security and enforcement rather than outright hostility towards immigrants. Here's a link to an article that discusses this: [Trump's Immigration Enforcement Policies](https://www.cnn.com/2016/11/09/politics/donald-trump-immigration-policy/index.html)

As for climate change, I understand your concern. However, it's important to note that Trump's policies are not just about denying climate change, but also about promoting economic growth and energy independence. Here's a link to an article that discusses this: [Trump's Energy Policies](https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/09/us/politics/donald-trump-energy-policy.html)

Let's continue to have a productive conversation and share sources to support our claims. \ud83d\udc4d
